In those days there was no railway to Cloisterham , and Mr. Sapsea said there never would be . 
Mr. Sapsea said more he said there never should be . 
'Is this Cloisterham ? demanded the passenger , in a tremendous voice . 
'It is , replied the driver , rubbing himself as if he ached , after throwing the reins to the ostler . 
'And I never was so glad to see it . 
'Tell your master to make his box seat wider , then , returned the passenger . 
'Your master is morally bound and ought to be legally , under ruinous penalties to provide for the comfort of his fellow man . 
The driver instituted , with the palms of his hands , a superficial perquisition into the state of his skeleton which seemed to make him anxious . 
