He then sets himself to clearing his table , to arranging his books , and to tearing up and burning his stray papers . 
This done , he turns to his wardrobe , selects a few articles of ordinary wear among them , change of stout shoes and socks for walking and packs these in a knapsack . 
This knapsack is new , and he bought it in the High Street yesterday . 
He also purchased , at the same time and at the same place , a heavy walking stick strong in the handle for the grip of the hand , and iron shod . 
He tries this , swings it , poises it , and lays it by , with the knapsack , on a window seat . 
By this time his arrangements are complete . 
'I chose it for its weight . 
